# PR Atlas

Vite 8 + React 19 + TypeScript 5.9 SPA for interview prep. Searches technology topics and shows matching GitHub PR examples. Uses pnpm, react-router v7, Recharts, Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite`, no JS config), react-i18next (EN/ES), Vitest 4, React Testing Library, ESLint 9, and Prettier with Tailwind class sorting.

## Key paths

- `src/app/App.tsx` — router shell: defines routes, lazy-loads DashboardPage
- `src/app/Layout.tsx` — shared layout: nav bar with active links + language switcher + `<Outlet>`
- `src/pages/SearchPage.tsx` — search page: debounced search, URL sync, focus management
- `src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx` — coverage dashboard: Recharts charts, lazy-loaded
- `src/data/sections.ts` — 180+ topics in compact section format (source of truth, rarely changes)
- `src/data/topics.ts` — pull requests, PR↔topic mappings (with feature labels), and `buildTopics` (update here when adding a PR)
- `src/lib/search.ts` — token-based search (lowercase, collapsed whitespace, all-terms match)
- `src/lib/highlight.ts` — text highlighting for matched terms
- `src/lib/storage.ts` — typed localStorage wrapper (get/set/remove with JSON serialization)
- `src/lib/use-saved-searches.ts` — saved searches hook (persist, deduplicate, cap at 20)
- `src/lib/url-state.ts` — `?q=` query-string parsing and updates
- `src/lib/use-debounced-value.ts` — 250ms debounce hook (two-layer state: `inputQuery` / `activeQuery`)
- `src/i18n/index.ts` — i18next configuration (language detection, localStorage persistence, bundled translations)
- `src/i18n/locales/en.json` / `es.json` — English and Spanish translation files
- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — coverage stats computation (category, level, thresholds)
- `src/components/` — `SearchControls`, `SavedSearches`, `TopicTable`, `HighlightText`, `EmptyState`, `LanguageSwitcher`
- `src/components/charts/` — `CategoryBarChart`, `LevelPieChart`, `ThresholdBars` (Recharts)
- `src/types/topics.ts` — shared TypeScript models (`PullRequestId`, `TopicId` enums; `PR_FEATURES` const; `Feature`, `PrTopicMappings`, `TopicPr`, `Topic` types)
- `src/index.css` — Tailwind `@theme`, custom utilities (`panel-surface`, `fade-up`, `data-row`, `search-input`)

## Testing split

Tests live in `src/test/` and are split by responsibility:

- `search.test.ts` — search correctness and matching rules
- `highlight.test.ts` — highlight segmentation and edge cases
- `url-state.test.ts` — query-string parsing and URL updates
- `use-debounced-value.test.tsx` — debounce timing and flush
- `storage.test.ts` — localStorage wrapper edge cases
- `use-saved-searches.test.tsx` — saved searches hook behavior
- `i18n-setup.ts` — test helper that initializes i18n with English bundle
- `coverage.test.ts` — coverage stats computation
- `App.test.tsx` — integration: URL hydration, debounced results, clear, focus management, empty state, saved searches, language switching, navigation

## Tailwind conventions

- Use v4 token syntax: `text-(--color-text-primary)` not `text-[var(--color-text-primary)]`
- Prefer built-in scale utilities over arbitrary values (`rounded-4xl` not `rounded-[32px]`)
- Custom CSS classes in `src/index.css` are intentional — do not replace them
- Class ordering is handled by `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` (`pnpm format`)

## Change checklist

After every code change, verify:

1. **Tests** — update or add tests in the matching `src/test/` file for any changed logic. Run `pnpm test` to confirm.
2. **Docs** — update `README.md` and `docs/architecture.md` if the change affects folder structure, data model, search behavior, rendering strategy, state flow, or testing strategy.
3. **Tailwind notes** — update `docs/tailwind-notes.md` if new CSS conventions or custom classes are introduced.
4. **Types** — keep `src/types/topics.ts` in sync with any data-model changes.
5. **Lint and format** — run `pnpm lint` and `pnpm format` before finishing.
